          <div align="justify">
                <p align="left"><strong><font size="+1">South Carolina Confederate Relic Room
                and Military Museum</font></strong></p>
              </div>
          <blockquote>
            <div align="left">
              <p><a href="http://www.crr.sc.gov/support/mcrae/" target="_blank"><strong>The Colin J. McRae Papers</strong></a><strong> </strong>-
                        The McRae Papers will form the backbone for an exhibition
              linking South Carolina&#8217;s involvement in
                      Confederate banking, financing, purchasing, and supply
              for the entire Southern
                        war effort. The
                      exhibit will also detail what impact the importation of
              English goods through the blockade had on Confederate soldiers
              in the
                        field. This exhibit will open at the <strong>South Carolina Confederate
                      Relic Room and Military Museum</strong> during the national Civil War Sesquicentennial
                  Anniversary in 2011.</p>
